                <note rend="inline" type="source">314.115C43/179: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-02T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 2, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. Your 141 of October 31. Department agrees in substance to proposal of
                    Guatemalan Government but considers the name of the arbitrator should appear and
                    that the passage in question should read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="flushleft">“it is agreed by the two governments that this question
                            shall be submitted to Sir Herbert Sisnett, Chief Justice of British
                            Honduras as arbitrator. The question to be submitted to the arbitrator
                            is as follows.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
